                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">Fol. 4r: elaborate uncoloured horizontal ornamental band; interlaces, floral and anthropomorphic (an angel’s head) motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">Fol. 32r: elaborate coloured (red and black) horizontal ornamental band; interlaces, geometric and anthropomorphic (a head) motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">Fols. 13ra, 19ra, 25vb, 41rb, 55rb: elaborate, coloured (red and black) short horizontal ornamental bands; interlaces.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">Fols. 13ra, 19ra, 34rb, 34va, 39ra, 39vb, 41vb: small coloured (red and black) squared or round ornaments with a cross inside.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d6"/>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">The bands indicate the beginning of sections for Sundays of Lent.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d8">The small ornaments indicate the beginning of sections for feasts.</decoNote>
